summary: Hey, I am the daughter of my mother (that sounds really weird...)
title: Hey, I am the daughter of my mother (that sounds really weird...)
body:
I don’t know if I am doing these correctly but I try. Can you guys just shut up?

My mum for the last two days whining and bubbling more that usual so I must intervene and write the same what I told her

1. It’s a tv show. Really expensive one. And it needs to be more sweet than bitter. Because HBO still wants to make money on it after finale airing. And when you are unhappy, you will stop watching. Making a lof of people unhappy, you make a lot of people to stop watching and encourage others to watch.

2. Shipping is important. HBO is not CW but some groups really increase studio’s earnings. They can kill some of couples but not all. If they try, they will follow Martin’s instructions. And in that case Martin cannot decline. If there is a lot of complaints, D&D just told the truth and these ends up very nasty. Remember Castle? After all these producers and cast drama, everyone lose- studio, Fillion and Katic. And it wasn’t that expensive show. Well, Martin can be millioner and he has a lot of fanboys but these kind of scandal would smell really bad for years. Like Nightflyers - flop and disaster (if you wanna watch sth really good try Expanse, in my opinion Corey is better writer than Martin). Better say: Yeah, finale is so cheesy, I will write it better.

3. I remember leaks about episode 3. We burried half of the cast on Saturday. All those extras, collegues, cleaners etc. And we lost two additional guys. I don’t count Lyanna Mormont, she was more Internet meme than part of the cast. Theon died as a hero, everyone cried but let be honest, what dickless, former traitor, on a redemption road guy can do in generation’s saga? And Jorah - the example of friendzone, make Daenerys fragile. Fun fact - I think that Jorah will died of greyscale in books and it would be Barristan Selmy who will die during Winterfell battle. But you know, Iain Glenn is much more handsome so they kinda swing their fates.

4. I also remember two things - the article when I read that they even hire some of crew as extras in 8x06 to increase safety and NCW’s duck. That was perfect trolling from actor, always get me laugh. Don’t analize what they said or what they wrote, no one wants lose their job.

5. I admit episode 4 was shitty. I think it’s because first three episodes was still in the Winds of Winter and three others would be Dream of spring (or like first Martin’s draft said ,,Time for wolves”). D&D just want put the characters in final stage really quickly and they just cross out point by point like in you shop list. It doesn’t exactly work because character must developed through time. Jaime’s case is perfect example. I can understand that not all redemption road can be success (although sex scene I think was just for Braimie fans), and he could has some concers and doubts and eventually come back to Cersei but not during one episode! Even half of it! BTW I love Bronn in these. ,,Well, we have different path for Sam, what can we do with Reach, we cut all the Tyrells?” ,,Give it to Bronn, everyone likes him, everone will be happy”. Sorry, but it could be also case for Gendry and Arya, they have more important (and longer) relationship in two last books but D&D just cut it short in their list.

6. On the other thing knowing that Tyrion get his head cut (what is actually really possible) I think it would be enough bitter for studio. Audience wants a baby, at least one. I don’t think Gilly’s count. For now Daenerys not be shown beeing pregnant, her realtionship with Jon is still to incest for standards, Sansa with Tyrion’s death and lonely Arya doesn’t feel good. Well, there is always a chance of Martin’s nihilism so let’s see. But calmy :)

7. In the end, when we talking about best endings remember finale of ,,Six feet under” - just the flash forward, where everyone dies, so great, amazing, happy but little sad, real bittersweet - just masterpiece. Also HBO.

tags: i had to put it out there
summary:
Arya IS a Stark
Having Arya speak that line about not intending to come back to Winterfell was just plain wrong.
It’s always...
body:
Arya IS a Stark

Having Arya speak that line about not intending to come back to Winterfell was just plain wrong.

It’s always been about family for her, whether it was about trying her hardest to go back to it or pour all of herself and all the strength she had left in learning how to avenge it. She always loved home, and now that she has it again she would abandon it to never come back?

Family is the one thing that kept her anchored to herself and now she just… walks away without looking back? She leaves Winterfell and no one gives a damn?

Add to this the costume designer saying she is “not a stark anymore, she is just passing by” and you clearly see how they never really understood her character and probably never will.

Arya IS a Stark, and it’s because she is that she could never truly become no one, it’s because she does care, she does hurt, she does want a home and now they’re trying to take away even this from her.

I’m hoping she is at this part of her journey where she fully realizes what she could lose if she lets go of her feelings completely and understand that that has never been what she wanted, but at this point I don’t trust anyone anymore.

I just find disrespectful the superficiality with which they’ve almost always approached one of the most complex characters of the story.

body:
For the next two episodes…

Sophie Tuner said in an interview when asked if people will be satisfied with the ending “some will be… others not so much”, and with the reactions for the last two episodes I have a feeling a lot more people will not be happy with the ending, and that’s ok; I honestly haven’t hated the season so far, yes it’s a bit fast paced and I hope they are able to wrap everything up but I don’t think that makes it ‘bad writing’? Anyway for the next two episodes, don’t let others hate make you hide your satisfaction 🤷🏻‍♀️ if that makes sense

summary: I feel like I’m the only one who’s glad they cut Arya’s “I enjoy new experiences” line. I don’t know why people are upset over...
question: I feel like I’m the only one who’s glad they cut Arya’s “I enjoy new experiences” line. I don’t know why people are upset over it. It would’ve implied she was with gendry just for sex rather than because she was also attracted and had strong feelings for him
answer: i agree anon. i had to go searching for the clip after you sent me this. i didn’t realize there were lines cut from the scene. but i’m glad they did away with that implication. i think the writers wanted us to believe that’s all it was for her at first, but then they shouldn’t have let maisie playing arya look THAT in love with gendry. they’re endgame. it is known.
